	<td>PAST- CM met with the CL for a case management meeting. CL asked how their job is going. CL currently works at a warehouse but states they feel harassed at their new job. CL states there are staff that walk too closely behind them. CM asked if they talked to HR about it and CL has not yet. CM suggested for CL to set their boundaries and talk to their manager about. CM suggested for CL to let them know in a calm demeanor they are uncomfortable with people walking so near them and not outwardly accuse staff of harassment. CL agreed.  CL wants to look into other jobs as they feel uncomfortable working around men and only want to work around women. They looked into finding a job again at the mall. CM reminded there is the upcoming holiday season where more retail jobs should be available. CM also gave them a flyer for an upcoming job fair at the Oceanside Library. CL asked about Lived Experiences as they want to do their laundry there. CL tried calling on Saturday. CM looked at the hours and are closed on the weekend. The website states they're open from 10 AM- 7 PM and laundry hours are from 10 AM- 8 PM.CM asked about the CL's housing plans. CL eventually does want to rent out a room but then need stable income first.PRESENT- Saw client at the Vista humanity showers today. Client has been on her meds, seeing her psychiatrist and her therapist. She would like another opportunity to enter into the BC NC if possible. She is currently staying in her car and safe parking as well as renting a few hotel rooms in between. Client is currently working at a packaging company four hours a day.GOAL- client is looking to maintain her job, get into a program and potentially finish cosmetology school.</td>
	<td></td>
	
