	<td></td>
	<td>Tammie Momant</td>
	<td>PAST- Client called desperate for shelter and to get out of her car and off the streets. She said she has someone following her that is possibly stalking her out. She stated she was beat up on 7/11 as she was coming out of a friend's RV. She stated that she has no support system and that she has been to every agency and has been let down. Client states that she has not gotten her SSI or EBT for a minute but should be back on anytime. Met with client at the hotel and checked her out of her room. After discussing clients trauma, tragedies, vulnerability and crisis with her yesterday and today I presented client the best options for this time. Client was reluctant to say that she feels that others that are undeserving of housing and got housing before her. She's very disgruntled in regard to no housing benefits and the resources that she's been offered by several providers. Client declined my recommendation to Esperanza crisis center due to the fact that that would push her back in life. I asked client if she had ever completed a program, assessment etc and client could not say she has. Client states she has adjustment disorder. Overall, client sees that she should have a roof over her head ie: housing to benefit her in her wellness and to get back on her feet.  Client feels that she has been fit and that she would be a good candidate for housing and why hasn't anybody provided her with housing. Client stated that she was gonna head over to Exodus and meet with them after leaving the hotel. Plan:  Get off the streets and get into shelter.  Find affordable housing.Goals: part time job, affordable housing</td>
	<td></td>
	
</tr>




