<tr>
	<td>30433116</td>
	<td>8/20/25 4:39 PM</td>
	<td>6616 Miramar Rd </td>
	
	<td>0</td>
	<td>0</td>
	
	<td>Vista</td>
	<td>Vanessa Alvarez</td>
	<td>16</td>
	<td>Outreach</td>
	<td>Refused Services</td>
	<td></td>
	<td>Michele  Hernandez</td>
	<td>We provided transportation for client from the Buena Creek Navigation Center to her storage in Miramar. Client stated that she was in the North County area ie Encinitas so that she could retrieve services and food supply and that she actually kind of goes wherever. Client stated that she was evicted from her section 8 apartment, but that she had won her lawsuit per the her lawyer iand that she might potentially be able to reinstate her section 8 voucher. I offered client to go into the South County lighthouse shelter. Client declined stating that she does not want to bounce around because it is not good for her mental health. Client stated she has issues with her mental health. I then told her about the Esperanza crisis Center as well as the La Jolla crisis Center. Client also declined because she does not want to be somewhere for a few weeks and then have to move again. I did let her know that there is a success rate amongst clients and that working together towards goals could potentially get her back on track. Client stated that she thought she could stay at the Buena Vista navigation center for 120 days to save money so she could get a minivan to stay in. Client stated that she would be calling a lawyer so that she could sue the BCNC throwing her out. Client stated that she was very unhappy because she doesn't understand how we could just throw her to the streets. I then reiterated to the client that there are options so that she does not have to be out on the street.but again client declined. Client stated that she guesses she will be calling 911. I questioned client and asked her if she used that option before and client stated she had used it many many times before. </td>
	<td></td>
	
</tr>




