	<td>Past: Met with client at the hotel and checked her out of her room. After discussing clients trauma, tragedies, vulnerability and crisis with her yesterday and today I presented client the best options for this time. Client was reluctant to say that she feels that others that are undeserving of housing and got housing before her. She's very disgruntled in regard to no housing benefits and the resources that she's been offered by several providers. Client declined my recommendation to Esperanza crisis center due to the fact that that would push her back in life. I asked client if she had ever completed a program, assessment etc and client could not say she has. Client states she has adjustment disorder. Overall, client sees that she should have a roof over her head ie: housing to benefit her in her wellness and to get back on her feet.  Client feels that she has been fit and that she would be a good candidate for housing and why hasn't anybody provided her with housing. Client stated that she was goning to head over to Exodus and meet with them after leaving the hotel. Present:  Client came to the office upset stating the mental health provider Exodus would not help her and she is at the end of her rope.  I asked if she wanted to hurt herself and she stated no.  I just want a hotel and a place to stay.  I offered her a place to go and she turned it down. Gave client some food and a cup of coffee and listened to her for about 2 hours.  I told her that her Outreach Specialist would be he soon.  She stated she would return today but client was a no show. Client is in the ERF area and has everything except for her documentation from Social Security office clients just need her benefit letter.\</td>
	<td></td>
	
</tr>




