	<td>PAST Client Joyce Salazar her and significant other have been in their current apartment for approximately five years. Client was previously married and was in a domestic violence relationship with spouse. Client stated she had a CPS case for approximately six months with CPS coming in and out of her house every day.PRESENT-Met with client and significant other at Starbucks in Vista. Client states she has six children, sharing one child approx 3 years old with current significant other. Client states they have not paid rent as of June 2025 due to her having to purchase a car after her vehicle being repossessed. Client states that she has been in her current job for approximately two years and is currently working graveyard. Client states significant other had a DUI in March and a second DUI in April.Client dates that significant other takes and picks up children from school daily. VOT had discussion with client in regards to significant other driving under a suspended license and the danger of him driving. Client had been in communication with interfaith who was going to supply her family with assistance in supporting them financially to halt the eviction status. There has been a lack of communication between the landlord, tenant and interfaith with this leading client into eviction proceedings. Client states that landlord will not place an eviction on record if client hands over keys for unit and vacates the property by September 2, 2025. Client has shown VOT a few different ledgers, we are not quite sure what amount due is at this time. VOT will be in touch with interfaith and landlord. PLAN-for client to maintain current apartment. For clients significant other to get into a program/detox. </td>
	<td></td>
	
</tr>




