	<td>Danielle Gordon</td>
	<td>Danielle GordanB-Clt showed up to Vista Outreach office. OW was initially speaking with her, but asked SW to eval. Clt presented with disjointed speech and only small bouts of coherency. SW also noted pupils were the size of a pinhead needles, and clt could not maintain eye contact during conversation. Clt was also tense and described being frustrated and experiencing lack of help from other entities. I-SW and OW engaged in active listening, and attempted CBT technique to get clt to see the active addiction rather than hx. SW and OW attempted MI to get her into Serenity House for the evening. R-Clt expressed being initially willing to be housed, but not wanting to actively be involved in services that would help her stabilize to get to housing. The client started to show more signs of incoherency. P-SW and OW requested permission to contact her PO in order to aid her. Clt stated she was not interested in shelter tonight. Clt stated she didn't want to give us her phone number, but had OW's number and would reach out to him to follow up. </td>
	<td></td>
	
</tr>




