	<td>Street Case Management</td>
	<td></td>
	<td>Deanna Johnson</td>
	<td>PAST-: I encountered the clients as I was walking out of the riverbank. I asked him if they needed any kind of resources and they agreed they told me they were homeless. I asked them for their ID and the ID said Vista California and I proceeded to do an intake on them Client seemed stable and able to understand what I was talking to her about, going to take her to get her documents on Tuesday PRESENT-Encountered client over by the Days Inn hotel. Client was referred to client by team member Mario. Upon encounter, client stated that she had been feeling very ill for the previous three days. Client stated she had been throwing up, Etc. Client stated her and boyfriend Joe have been together off and on for 10 years. Client stated her and boyfriend have been staying in the non-running vehicle for 3 to 4 months. Client stated she was employed for 17 years by employer before she lost employment in housing that was also supplied by employer. Client stated she did have power attorney over employer, but due to a non-family member taking the assets to court she was then left homeless.Client stated that she has Crohn's disease and has had battles with cancer in the past. Client denied any substance use. we were able to take client's boyfriend to humanity showers, provide food for him as well as client upon arrival back at the Days Inn. PLAN-client to maintain stability, possible detox, and housing as well as employment</td>
	<td></td>
	
</tr>




