	<td></td>
	<td>Kristen Logan</td>
	<td>PRESENT-Client has been staying at the Buena Creek navigation center for approximately two weeks. Clients presence at the center and engaging in program has been limited due to clients in activity. Client seems to spend most of her time in the jungle. Client was advised by the shelter to return nightly and prior to Curfew. Client has missed curfew and not returned on several occasions. I spoke with client and advise her to follow the rules and participate in program and sign into McAllister as well. Client stated prior that she had no problem and was willing to connect with McAllister, today client declined their services. Client is advised to connect with Esperanza crisis center and or program detox. Client and is advised to engage in dual services.Client  stated to me that she is having difficulty with her new roommate. Client stated that she would like to have a room change at the shelter. I let client know that I would engage with the shelter on her behalf to see if things could be rectified, and she would have a room change option. The shelter will follow up with client.During our conversation, clients began to be very aggressive on the phone and unhappy with the services, and her current situation. Client is not understanding of the process and program/shelter that are available to her while she awaits housing. Client stated that she would like to know exactly when she'll be moved in to housing, with whom she can move into housing with I.e. ex boyfriend and/or husband, where she will be housed, if she can be housed with people that she knows, if she can have her pets, etc. Housing, navigator, and myself went over in detail what this could possibly look like for client in the near future. Client stated that she has been to rehab and has used various resources before and has been left back on the street. I assured client that if she were to work on her goals with the San Diego rescue Mission that this would not be the case. Our goal is to Shelter client, get her housed with wraparound services and put an end to her homelessness.  We have placed client in program/rehab twice client has left willingly not working the program.This is clients third time being placed in shelter. Client has a approximately one year-old dog that she is and is not willing to foster out or place with friends and family. This seems to be a huge barrier for client to get into any programs and or detox. Client has stated that this is her emotional support animal. Client has no documentation and the animal has not had any training to support this statement. </td>
	<td></td>
	
</tr>




